OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FIs it the end for the lush 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Flawns of Los Angeles?      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, "The era of the lush lawn is over,"    
OL,6, declares Lynne Toby, a pensioner who   
OL,7, has lived in Los Angeles for 40 years. 
OL,9,FMs Toby's attitude toward grass lawns  
OL,10,Fhas changed over the years. She wanted 
OL,11,Fa lawn when her son was young and      
OL,12,Fplaying sport. But once he stopped, she
OL,13,Flet it die.                            
OL,15,FThis was partly for practical reasons -
OL,16,Fas a lawn requires a great deal of     
OL,17,Fmaintenance. But the decision was also 
OL,18,Frelated to her interest in conserving  
OL,19,Fwater, amidst the persistent drought   
OL,20,Fconditions in Los Angeles, California. 
